---
import ImageComparisonSlider from "./ImageComparisonSlider.astro";
import baseImage from "../assets/images/profile-featup.png";
import overlayImage from "../assets/images/profile.png";
import { LINKEDIN_HANDLE } from "../config";
---

<section class="w-full max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div class="text-center mb-12 sm:mb-16">
    <h1
      class="font-extrabold text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl tracking-tight mb-4"
    >
      <span
        class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#fb923c] via-[#f97316] to-[#ea580c] dark:from-primary-main dark:via-primary-main dark:to-primary-main bg-clip-text text-transparent"
      >
        Alex Lavaee
      </span>
    </h1>
    <p
      class="text-lg sm:text-xl lg:text-2xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 font-light"
    >
      Engineer. Researcher. Lifelong learner.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div
    class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-8 lg:gap-16 flex-1"
  >
    <div class="w-full max-w-sm flex flex-col items-center">
      <div class="w-full flex-col justify-center">
        <ImageComparisonSlider
          baseImageSrc={baseImage}
          overlayImageSrc={overlayImage}
          baseImageAlt="Pixelated Profile picture"
          overlayImageAlt="Regular Profile picture"
          initialPosition={33}
          sliderWidth="w-64 sm:w-80 lg:w-[350px] xl:w-[400px]"
          sliderHeight="h-64 sm:h-80 lg:h-[350px] xl:h-[400px]"
          instructionText={`
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">
              Slide to view <a
                href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2403.10516"
              class="underline hover:text-primary-main">feature image</a
              >
            </p>
          `}
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div
      class="w-full max-w-xl lg:max-w-lg mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 text-center lg:text-left overflow-y-auto max-h-[600px] px-4 py-2 custom-scrollbar"
    >
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Hey there! üëãüèº I'm Alex, an incoming software engineer @ Microsoft. I'm
        interested in solving problems in AI/ML infra (ML optimization,
        distributed systems), AI4Science (scientific discovery), and robotics
        (world models + perception systems).
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
        I completed my data science undergrad @ BU where I was fortunate to work
        with Prof <a
          href="https://www.bu.edu/cs/profiles/betke/"
          class="text-primary-main hover:text-primary-dark font-medium transition-colors"
          >Margrit Betke</a
        > at the Image and Video Computing Group on a 3D self-supervised representation
        learning model for understanding human motion. üèÉüèº‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è During my final year of
        undergrad I had the opportunity to work with Prof <a
          href="https://cellbio.hms.harvard.edu/faculty-staff/tomas-kirchhausen"
          class="text-primary-main hover:text-primary-dark font-medium transition-colors"
          >Tomas Kirchhausen</a
        > @ Harvard Medical School where I developed, DINO3D, a 3D self-supervised
        representation learning model for understanding the molecular and cellular
        world. üß¨
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Previously, I interned as a SWE, MLE, and data scientist at Microsoft,
        Boeing, Edwards Lifesciences (where I developed an FDA processing model
        for severe aortic stenosis detection @ The Applied Machine Learning
        Group), and AI startups (including Themis AI, an MIT CSAIL spinoff
        backed by Prof Daniela Rus), gaining hands-on experience in developing
        scalable AI products.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Finally, feel free to reach out and connect on
        <a
          href={`https://linkedin.com/in/${LINKEDIN_HANDLE}`}
          class="text-primary-main hover:text-primary-dark font-medium transition-colors"
          >LinkedIn</a
        > or email at lavaalex3 [at] gmail [dot] com. I look forward to collaborating
        and sharing ideas! Finally, check out my <a
          href="/projects"
          class="text-primary-main hover:text-primary-dark font-medium transition-colors"
          >projects</a
        >!
        <span class="font-bold">&lt|endoftext|&gt</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
